Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/definedBy
Object: Relates a constituency area to the boundary set it was defined by.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/Country
Object: A country in the United Kingdom.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/CombinedAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which a combined authority may exercise its powers. A combined authority may be created in England under powers set out in the Local Democracy, Economic Development and Construction Act 2009.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/isAlsoUpperTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: Relates a lower tier local authority area to an upper tier local authority area where the lower tier local authority area is also the upper tier local authority area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/establishedBy
Object: Relates a geographic area established by statute to the statutory thing it was established by.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/appliesFrom
Object: Relates a boundary set to the date that boundary set applies from.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/geometry
Object: Relates a geographic area to the geometry describing the boundaries of that area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/boundarySetEstablishedBy
Object: Relates a boundary set to the statutory thing it was established by.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/StatutoryThing
Object: A statutory thing, for example: an Act of Parliament or a made statutory instrument.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/ons_code
Object: Relates a geographic area to its code as assigned by the Office of National Statistics.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/UpperTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which an upper tier local authority may exercise its powers.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/ConstituencyArea
Object: The geographic area of a UK Parliament constituency.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/LowerTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: The geographic area in which a lower tier local authority may exercise its powers.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/
Object: A model describing geographic areas in the UK - being constituency areas, local authority areas, countries, and statistical regions within England - and the containment relationships between such areas.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/BoundarySet
Object: A boundary set for UK Parliament constituency areas, as proposed in a boundary review by the Boundary Commission and established by statute.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/partlyContainedBy
Object: Relates a geographic area to a geographic area it is partly contained by. A constituency area may be partly contained by a lower tier local authority area, by an upper tier local authority area, or by neither. A lower tier local authority area or an upper tier local authority area may be partly contained by a constituency area. The Local Democracy, Economic Development and Construction Act 2009 does not preclude an upper tier local authority area being partly contained by a combined authority area. As at November 2021, no upper tier local authority area is partly contained by a combined authority area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/GeographicAreaEstablishedByStatute
Object: A geographic area established by an Act of Parliament or a made statutory instrument.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/whollyContainedBy
Object: Relates a geographic area to the geographic area it is wholly contained by. A constituency area may be wholly contained by a lower tier local authority area, by an upper tier local authority area, or by neither. A constituency area in England is wholly contained by an English region. A constituency area is wholly contained by a country. A lower tier local authority area may be wholly contained by a constituency area. A lower tier local authority area is wholly contained by an upper tier local authority area, except where the lower tier local authority area is also the upper tier local authority area. An upper tier local authority area may be wholly contained by a constituency area. As at November 2021, an upper tier local authority area is wholly contained by a combined authority area, where a combined authority area exists.An upper tier local authority area in England is wholly contained by an English region. An upper tier local authority area is wholly contained by a country. A combined authority area may be wholly contained by an English region. A combined authority area is wholly contained by the country of England. An English region is wholly contained by the country of England.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/EnglishRegion
Object: A statistical region in England being a UK International Territorial Level (ITL).

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/geographic-area/isAlsoUpperTierLocalAuthorityArea
Object: Is also upper tier local authority area
